°C) until browned, covering and setting aside once done. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and continue with recipe."},{"content":"Place cassava in mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Add coconut milk, sugar, oil and cornflour then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Add coconut and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Divide mixture between prepared moulds and place in Varoma dish then cover with Varoma lid and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water and remaining 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl."},{"content":"Insert simmering basket and weigh in rice. Place Varoma into position then steam <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Remove Varoma and unmould quindim. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Reserve 190 g cooking water and discard rest. Transfer cooked rice to a serving bowl. Pour over reserved cooking water and stir with spatula. Cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Place remaining 1 garlic clove, 100 g onions and 30 g olive oil in mixing bowl, chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add spinach, peas and carrots then sauté <b>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to serving bowl with rice and stir together with spatula. Serve vegetable rice with tofu meatballs. Enjoy quindims for dessert."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Quindim is a classic Brazilian dessert made of set coconut and custard. Typically presented as an upturned cup, it is dense with a glistening appearance and is intensely sweet and addictive!"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 35m","6 portions"]}